title: Remove failed check notification if we successfully check and it is present.…
message: Remove failed check notification if we successfully check and it is present. Patiently try five times to get the last tor message if we get an io error - tor may be starting up and should recover quickly. If tor is down, we bail out of five times and return the io error code. This resolves the frequent 'yellow exclamation' when tor first boots up.

title: Refactor setUserChecking to setSkipNextCheck. Ensure that receiver resets skip…
message: Refactor setUserChecking to setSkipNextCheck. Ensure that receiver resets skip check if service already running to avoid repeating skips.

title: Change isUserChecking to more general isSkipNextCheck. Make the service skip…
message: Change isUserChecking to more general isSkipNextCheck. Make the service skip checks on the first pass. This is a conservative approach that will ensure if we've just been killed and get an alarm we won't fire when we shouldn't. If no network volatility occur between alarms, we'll successfully check on the first time. This should help us be nicer to Tor when connections are going up and down and also reduce Tor broken nags, e.g., on bootup. Additionally, remove dependency on torproxylib.jar and yank SocksProxy class into our project. This will give more control in the future if we need it and reduce the jar dependency. Add 15s SO_TIMEOUT to socket and keepalive.

title: Create notification if new message service fails to check two times in a row.…
message: Create notification if new message service fails to check two times in a row. This will let people know if the new messages aren't coming through. If it is too aggressive (i.e., notifies too soon), we can tweak the logic.
